rComments: I didn't do the readings and attended his class, ended up with A-. I love this prof, so funny and the class is much more manageable size. Would love to take another class with him.

Exciting, fun lectures, very inspirational. Heavy on reading, learned lots of new stuff. Makes sure you attend TA sessions, very helpful. I wish we had a mid-term exam though. Final exam is 3 essays, covering almost 300 years :)

One of the most amazing Profs you will ever meet. Hilarious, charismatic, and caring about students. His lectures are super well-explained and informative. The readings can be heavy and you don't necessarily have to do them, but you should. Fair final exam and you write 2 essays. Tutorial participation is important.

This is one of the best profs I have had at UofT. He is super engaging and knows a lot about the subject matter. That being said, it is in your best interest to attend lecture, as there are lots of little details on the exam that were included in lecture and not the textbook. Honestly lecture In this course was so fun, you won't want to miss it.
One of the most intelligent and amazing profs I've had at Uoft.

Prof Dimitriadis is one of the best profs I've had in UofT. He's very passionate about what he teaches and very approachable. He's willing to go extra miles for his students. Make sure to go to his Friday movie sessions whenever possible (if he still does it); he introduced me to some of the greatest films in history.
One of the greatest lecturers
Amazing professor.

One of the best lecturers in the History department. He really makes an art of it. Hilarious personal anecdotes were a nice touch! He also deeply cares that students  do well, so he gives pretty detailed feedback on essays/assignments. Also an insanely fair marker - as long as you've clearly made an effort, you'll get a good mark.

Friendly and very accessible outside class time. I enjoyed his class very much - though I have only one issue - that is with the constant Trump bashing. Considering the divided social climate we are in, I noticed that many students didn't feel comfortable with his take on politics  and I think his views were better suited for outside the classroom

He's the first professor I've had at the university to show such genuine compassion for what he teaches. He's extremely approachable and encourages students to ask him for questions or help. I've brought friends to his lectures and they're inspired. I don't know another professor at the university that's as knowledgable and compassionate as he is.

My favourite first-year professor, his dynamic lectures made what could have been a very dry subject into something really engaging, like a good novel. Sometimes they can get a bit convoluted but he is always happy to answer any questions. A cool guy too, make sure you go out to his pub nights when you get the chance.

This professor is an engaging lecturer but do not take this course if you want to take anything unbiased (or as unbiased as a single person can be). Hideously anti-communist and no nuance to his thoughts or views whatsoever. Seems like he didn't learn anything past what Ontario students learn in middle school and high school. Waste of time, sadly.
Really good prof. Lectures were great, felt like I was watching a documentary. I thought his treatment of the Cold War was pretty even-handed. Expectations on assignments were pretty reasonable.
Amazing lectures. Poorly crafted assignments. TAs are over worked and expectations are not clearly defined.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'So many papers', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Amazing prof. Highly recommend taking his course. His lectures are straightforward and clear, people clap at the end of EVERY lecture. Easily got an 83 in this course. Exams and essays are straightforward. Had him during the TA strike and he took the time to see everybody who needed it about their essays. Best prof I've had at U of T, love him.

Brilliant and funny professor! Extremely passionate about what he teaches and is very approachable if you have any questions or want to discuss current issues with him. The course was so interesting and his anecdotes were great supplements to the lecture. Looking for another course he teaches that I can take

BY far the best professor I've had at UofT;  he showed immense interest in the subject matter and as such made going to lecture something to look forward to each week.  As much as the course itself was interesting he made it even better. Definitely would take another one of his courses.
Love this prof! Took another history class simply because he was teaching it.
Absolutely amazing prof, very passionate and knowledgeable about what he teachers. Lectures are always fun and informative.

lovelovelove this professor. He is so passionate about what he teaches and really knows what he's talking about. Very friendly & willing to meet with students to help. Tutorial participation is a big chunk of the mark though (20%)
Amazing lecturer. Doesn't need a powerpoint to lecture and you can really feel his passion. He also has no surprises for his evaluations.

Students tend to love this professor because he is funny. However, the fun comes at the price of meaningful lectures. His neoliberal interpretation of the Cold War was simplistic, one-sided, not nuanced, and uncritically biased. There were also factual errors in his lectures. I took his course because it was required, but would not have otherwise.

What a great guy! Taught the intensive and condensed yearlong course and made it comfortable. He is funny, calm, and relaxed. Knows his stuff, and loves when you answer his questions. Just a happy guy! Exam was a breeze; He said he HATES trying to trick students! Amazing. Take his courses. Invites class out to the pub too!
Really great prof. Really interesting course, really dedicated and opinionated, great guy.

Handedly the most influential individual to my university education. I have taken a class with him every semester since I had him for HIS103 in my first year. Always interesting, no surprises on exams, endless opportunities to excel. I have also attended different talks he has given outside of class. Truly the best professor in the HIS department.

I ABSOLUTELY ADORE THIS MAN. Extremely knowledgeable and funny. You can tell he really cares about his students and is more than willing to engage the class in discussion. Always has the best pre-class jokes and explains things in simple terms so as to make sure everyone understands. Great Guy.

Really he was professor I've ever had. His lectures are interesting and easy to follow. I wasn't always able to make it on time so I appreciated the fact that he does good recaps the following lesson. He just has a way of getting you to be passionate about the subject and understand the broader significance.

enthusiastic lecturer. loved listening to him. however, hated taking notes in his class. i always take notes by hands. but, with his speed, and accent, this class was the first (and only) i would bring my laptop to in a bid to keep up with him. even then, my notes were generally disorderly and confusing when it came time to study

The clearest, kindest, most caring prof I've ever had. I can't express how much this man is worth. Granted much of the lecture material is direct repetition of text, but just sit in awe of his command of that material, and his jokes and accent while you're at it. Also, very approachable. Approach him and just chat, you won't regret it.
Very good temporary replacement for Prof. Smyth! Knows his stuff and how to relate the past to the present to make it easier to understand what was going on back then.

BEST PROF EVER! If you can take his courses then do so. He makes the material interesting, has engaging lectures, funny jokes, is helpful, and knows EVERYTHING. He's VERY knowledgeable. LOVE this class and its because of Vasilis! It doesn't hurt that he's also one of the coolest profs. If it were up to me he would teach every IR course at UofT.
Amazing prof. Best I've had at UofT.

Best Prof that I have had at UofT. The class was engaging even though there were so many people in it. He was funny and very smart as he memorizes every single lecture. His accent can be difficult at first but still and amazing guy.

Naturally, Dimitriadis is an absolute boss. He memorizes every lecture, cares deeply about his students and is just really funny. His accent can make it difficult to understand certain treaty names/leaders, but he was without a doubt, my favourite professor this year!
Best Prof I've had so far. Engaging, funny, and incredibly intellectual. My T.A for this class was wonderful too, best learning experience I've had so far at UofT. Just a great guy
by far the best professor i've ever had.
Dimitriadis is one of the best profs at U of T.

"Part and parcel..." if you know what that is, you know Dimitriadis. Best. Prof. Ever. While the course covers 300 years of history & has dense readings, he never oversimplifies it, just makes it lively and clear. Very engaging, funny (you can literally have a beer with this guy), & knowledgeable, doesn't need notes to lecture. Outstanding!

Dimitriadis is easily one of the best professors at U of T. He's passionate about the subject, incredibly well spoken, and very sympathetic to his students. He also tells a good joke. Very highly recommended!

He's fun, interesting and a really good lecturer. While the topic sometimes gets boring, he's interesting enough to keep you awake. HIs lectures are loads of fun and he almost always has a joke ready.
NICEST. HOTTEST PROF AT U OF T
An amazing professor and human being. Such a pleasure to be in his class!
awsome

An excellent professor! Very knowledgeable and engaging. Encourages students to participate. His lectures are well-structured (but do not provide too much detail) and the tutorials are fun. He is a fair marker (expect to get a lot of feedback) and is genuinely interested in helping students improve their grades. The final exam is okay (no tricks).
An excellent professor: conscientious; clearly cares about his students; conducts his own tutorials; and even screened historically-relevant films outside of class time; A+!!
Simply put, the best professor i've ever had. Knowledgeable yet down to earth and just a cool guy all in all.

A real educator in every sense of the word. If the history department or the institution of U of T doesn't show him the respect and admiration that he deserves then they are really losing out (and in turn many future minds that will benefit from his tutelage).

Probably the best history prof ever. Seriously. Lectures are heavy on content. Always has a joke before class, and a summary of terms on the board. Real value in the awesome lectures, though. If you can write fast, you can benefit. Plus, he is just the coolest guy you will ever have as a lecturer.

I took 2 of his classes (HIS241 and EUR200.) He was excellent both times! In the EUR200 class he knew everyone by name because he was the TA (and the class was smaller.) He was always happy to help and interested in what you had to say. I learned a lot in his classes and he made his lectures clear and thus easy to make connections. Great prof!

INCREDIBLE PROFESSOR! I went into the course knowing that when it comes to histories, the professor is everything & I was not dissapointed! He did an amazing job outlining & making European history really interesting! I would definately recommend. :)

Best prof you will ever have. Hilarious jokes, amazing tutorials, really interesting essay topics, clear lectures- he knows his stuff. One of the few profs who really cares about the students he teaches.

Amazing professor, of the highest quality: Combines humour, insight, clarity and constancy to make the class a joy --everytime--without exceptions. Workload is about expected. He changed my life! Took his class once, immediately committed to take all his 3 classes next year. He's a good man of dignity, integrity, and humour.
AMAZING

He was very knowledgeable, clear, interesting, and funny. His exam was a bit challenging, but the readings were reasonable. He never gave pointless assignments, and the TAs had great attitudes as well.

Amazing teacher. Enthusiastic about the material, extremely helpful, and always has great jokes!! He explains the course curriculum very well and does not make you do tedious assignments or dumb papers. I loved his teaching style and how much he cared about the students.

Best Prof Yet!!! Helps whenever possible! Very clear on his concepts - Tests are very straightforward and if you show up to class you will know exactly what will be on the exam. Tutorials worth 20% - Great TAs too!
his lectures are absolutely amazing. crystal clear. He is the man. love his jokes.

Holy frick, the classes flow nice and the tutorials are run by him. Best course so far in university, by a long shot too. It's not awfully hard and you come out smarter. And happier. And, in my case, hungry because it was lunch time.
WONDERFUL prof!!  He teaches very well.  When I had him in first year, I didn't realise that he truly was a gem.  Very rare in his teaching style - truly excellent.  STRONGLY recommend!

Really helpful and willing to meet personally with students. Online notes would have been helpful for keeping up with the dense lectures. High expectations for a first year course: 2, 3000 word essays, tutorial participation, and a 3hr 3 essay exam. Easy to study for the final though. Overall: great prof, tough 1st year course.

Extremely knowledgeable, captivating speaker, Teaches all of the tutorials... Course load is moderate to light: 2 3000 word Essays worth 25%; 15% participation mark; 35% Final... Grading is fair; Final Exam changes very little year to year. Course material: European History from the Peace of Westphalia to WWII; focus is on international relations.
Amazing professor.  Good with everything, very helpful, approachable.  Wow.  One of my favourite professors.  Very nice guy.  If you happen to get this professor you're in for a fun time.

Had limited knowledge of the subject matter before this course, but he made it easy to manage. Seems to love what he does. Great guy, always helpful and encouraging. Best prof and ta yet. Take this course .... stay on top of the reading though. Bit demanding with the essays....3000 words...it is an introductory first year course...bit much to ask .
great prof, couldent have asked for more, best guy ever hahha, good jokes
Vasilis is the man!
Good guy
HEY VASILIS, it is luca zucal, just wanted to tel you i love you, and tell vassell i say wassup.  Best Prof in the world, VASILIS cant be beat!!!
A great prof!
Vasilis you are the man. Jokes are hillarious. Great guy both in and out of the classroom. Recommended to everyone. I would be his baby's momma!
Vasilis is a relaxed, funny man.  Don't you want the prof who speaks seven languages and has the best jokes?   Of course you do.

The BEST professor and TA I've had this year (and perhaps throughout my univ. life). He is extremely helpful and down to earth. His witty humour is mixed with his great proficiency of the course subject-matter which made the class enjoyable. I would definitely take another class that he teaches.

Probably the best professor ever. Very fair, nice, funny... He always had great jokes in class. Not the type to try and trip you up, he just wants everyone to do their best. I would definitely take something with him again.

Vasilis was the best teacher that I had in my first year.  He lives for his subject and loves what he teaches.  He tells jokse at the end of each class that is borderline appropriate but they are hilarious and everyone enjoys them a lot! He's awesome...I'd marry him
Vasilis is a king among men, and master of the hard-hitting punchline.  I worship him.
He is so intelligent and knows his stuff, and really seems to care about his topic. He goes so quickly though, and I often don't catch what's going on. The jokes are a plus!

This guy is amazing and the classes are so interesting! His analysis and explanation make the topic so clear to understand, plus his jokes in relation with recent events, is just a proof of how smart this guy is! I don't read the book, but just go to the lectures and totally understand the topic! :)

oh man, you must be doing something wrong if you are not enjoying this course, this is one of the best courses around and its got the best instructor teaching it. Vasilis is knowledgeable, funny, outgoing, and everything you would expect in a great prof.

This guy is probably one of the best teachers I've ever had. He's so unbelievably clear with everything that no one should have a problem understanding. His jokes are hilarious and really give the lecture that extra...zing to "cheer you up" as he would say. Plus, he's Greek, baby! Boo ya!!

Vasilis man! u rock!! as a course co-ordinator you have the skills! even though you're only a course co-ordinator, you'll be a prof one day, i know it!!! good luck with that! and by and large, it's been a blast!
Makes History fun to learn.  Keeps the students' interest the entire class.  Very funny.  GREAT PROF!
Surprise, surprise, he gets high marks from me.  Kudos to the other person quoting his sayings.
amazing prof! Clear, interesting, punctual, animated and brilliant. Also, he tells Bush jokes to end every class! I would definitely suggest him to anyone.

Great Prof. Took 1st year History with him. Amazing sense of humour. Course material was very interesting. Even the final exam was good. He divided the course into two time periods, so it was easy to learn. Recommend his class to everybody.
By and large, he is a great prof.
Very Good, and very clear
He is very smart. Can show connections between Louis XIVth's and Bush's wars.

Vasilis is incredibly knowledgable about this subject.  Moreover, he conveys his knowledge with exceptional clarity and wit.  As a lecturer, he is superb.  In the tutorials, he is a Godsend, helping us all to achieve our very best.
BEST PROF SO FAR!
we like him
The best prof at the uni as far as im concerned. Not only is he brilliant, he truly cares about getting every student to fully understand the material.

Terrific teacher! He knows his material extremely well; his lectures are very well organized and interesting. His tutorials are excellent as well. He challanges your ideas in a way to generate class discussion, and NOT to shoot you down. AWESOME TEACHER!
A good teacher - loves to joke, and very helpful

Great teacher, not so great in tutorials (tended to try and lead us by the nose). Really knows his stuff, and cares about teaching it - but watch out for his jokes, which he occasionally slips into the main lecture (they're funny, but can disrupt notes).

Absolutely wonderful prof. extremely approachable and dedicated, passionate about the material, has a very warm personality. He is harsh very rarely, and only to students who are either extremely stupid, or show no interest in the material.
No Comments
Vasilis is a great teacher, very humorous and friendly with thorough knowledge of the material, excellent to debate with.
I didn't find him condescending in any way. He cares about his students and the material. great prof
Vasilis is an excellent teacher -- he might be harst at times, although this professor knows his history
he's harsh and condescending.. but sometimes nice. strange man
somewhat of a misogynist, makes students feel quite inferior
